-- India Declares on 521-8 Against England in First Cricket Test
-- B y   C h r i s t o p h e r   E l s e r
-- 2012-11-16T10:05:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-16/india-declares-on-521-8-against-england-in-first-cricket-test.html
India  declared on 521-8 as
Cheteshwar Pujara hit a double century, putting  England  in to
bat on the second day of their first cricket Test in Ahmedabad.  Pujara was 206 not out, joined by Pragyan Ojha with no
runs, at the end of the innings. Graeme Swann was 5-144, and
also had a catch for England.  Opening batsman Nick Compton, whose grandfather played for
England, is making his debut, while Samit Patel will bat at No.
6 and bowled left-arm spin.  Yuvraj Singh  returned to India’s
Test lineup for the first time in a year after recovering from a
rare germ cell cancer.  The match is the first of four between the teams. England,
which swept the best-of-four contest when the teams last met in
the U.K., hasn’t won a Test series in India since 1984-85.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Christopher Elser at 
 celser@bloomberg.net  